org.jhove2.core.source
Interface Source

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Source>, Reportable
All Known Subinterfaces:
MeasurableSource, NamedSource
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractSource, ArcRecordSource, ByteStreamSource, ClumpSource, DirectorySource, FileSetSource, FileSource, URLSource, WarcRecordSource
public interface Source
extends Reportable, Comparable<Source>

Interface for JHOVE2 source units. A source unit is a formatted object that can be characterized, which may be a file, a subset of a file, or a group of files.

Author:
mstrong, slabrams, smorrissey

addChildSource

Source addChildSource(Source child)
                      throws JHOVE2Exception
Add a child source unit. Must ensure that child source's getParentSource() will return this source After method s1.addChildSource(c1)completes, it should be the case that, for Sources s1, s2, and c1, if s1.getChildren().contains(c1)==true, && s2.getChildren().contains(c1)==true, then s1==s2

Parameters:
child - Child source unit
Returns:
Child Source
Throws:
JHOVE2Exception

getParentSourceId

Long getParentSourceId()
Convenience method for SourceAccessors that use "foreign key" semantics for sourceId fields. It is the responsibility of SourceAccessor to maintain any "foreign key" semantics that its persistence model makes use of to relate a Source's parent Source to parentSourceId field Preferred method for access to parent Source is Source.getParentSource()

Returns:
the moduleParentSourceId, or null if this Source has no Parent

setParentSourceId

Source setParentSourceId(Long parentSourceId)
                         throws JHOVE2Exception
Set parentSourceId field. Convenience method for SourceAccessors that use "foreign key" semantics for sourceId and parentSourceId fields. It is the responsibility of SourceAccessor to maintain any "foreign key" semantics that its persistence model makes use of to relate a Source's parent Source to parentSourceId field The preferred method for setting a child source (childSource)'s parent to parentSource is parentSource.addChildSource(childSource); to remove a child (setting child's parent to null) is parentSource.deleteChildSource(childSource). Changing a Source's parent should be accomplished via a sequence of method invocations: first oldParentSource.deleteChildSource(childSource); then newParentSource.addChildSource(childSource).

Parameters:
parentSourceId - value to be set
Returns:
Source child Source whose parent has been reset
Throws:
JHOVE2Exception
